{
 "name": "RPlog_SW1_Log_2000-08-07-2",
 "title": "Suspicions About John Donivan",
 "summary": "In the computer center of New Republic Intelligence headquarters, the spymaster Kathryn Jrevelian reviews incoming reports from her passive agents when Bazil McKenzie arrives to catch up after weeks buried in administrative duties left to him by the absent Director. The two trade wry banter about the wild rumors of Bazil's fate and update each other on ongoing operations -- the Pallando team's reports, the Caspar group, the Death Star threat, and Xanatos's plan to seize the Angry Rancor for Imperial reconnaissance. Bazil then turns serious, voicing his deep distrust of John Donivan, the OREO CEO who controls the Republic's banking system and once employed him, and asks Kathryn to help gather intelligence on the man's corrupt reach. Kathryn, agreeing he is too powerful and surely guarded, offers to tap her contact Troy for dirt while she is on Caspar, and the pair part to pursue the investigation.",
